HEADWORD: Caladium
<hw>Ca*la"di*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.]</ety>
<def>A genus of aroideous plants, of which some species are cultivated
for their immense leaves (which are often curiously blotched with white
and red), and others (in Polynesia) for food.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Calaite</ent>⟦br⟧
